snippet.textDisplay:
I would just like to point out that as absurd as the dimensions are for this glorious machine that I absolutely adore, there is one car that dwarfs even this thing.

My favorite car of all time; the 1929 Bugatti Type 41 Royale Coupe de Napoleon. (Although the Kellner Coupe and the Coupe de Ville Binder are tempting.)

It has about a 6in longer wheelbase than the G63 6x6, and is, somehow, almost a full two feet longer at 21ft.

Just goes to show you, when it comes to opulence, ostentatiousness, bravado, and High-End-Luxury-Weaponized-Absurdism, you still cant beat the Bugatti Royale.

Dont believe me? Look for yourself- https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bugatti_Royale
